Still in Ueno, my fiancé and I lunched the next day at Danki Tonkatsu in
Asakusa. I found this place once years wandering around Asakusa scouting for
tonkatsu shops; neither time I ate here did it disappoint. After this I walked
to Skytree while others took the train. I have fond memories walking along the
Sumida river so I was far from bored on the walk there. I had been to Skytree
just once, during Golden Week. Unfortunately Skytree tickets were sold out at
that time so I just walked around Skytree City and went home. This time we
pre-ordered tickets for both the tower and the aquarium.

